cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with object detection using deep convolutional neural networks. It also involves transfer learning, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes an algorithm that learns the difference between classification and detection tasks and transfers this knowledge to classifiers. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with developing algorithms that can enable detection for categories that lack bounding box annotations. 

Natural language processing (cs.CL) and multimedia (cs.MM) are less likely sub-categories, but they cannot be completely ruled out as the paper involves processing large quantities of image-level labels and evaluating the efficacy of the proposed algorithm on the ImageNet LSVRC-2013 detection challenge.
